The Speaker of the National Assembly Justin Muturi has directed the Departmental Committee on Defence and Foreign Relations to approve the names of the appointed Ambassadors, High Commissioners and Permanent Representatives The Speaker said that he received the a letter from President Uhuru Kenyatta containing the names of the 22  persons for appointment. "The message conveyed is seeking the National Assembly’s approval of the persons for appointment to the offices of Ambassadors, High Commissioners and Permanent Representatives to the stations specified," Muturi's letter read. The 22 were appointed by the President on April 22. The names listed include; Clement Nzomo Kiteme who is proposed to be an ambassador to Angola, Mary Mugwanja to Austria among others. The High Commissioners appointed include Michael Sialai to Namibia, Major General Andrew Ikenye to Nigeria and others in the list below. Permanent Representatives appointees include Richard Bosire to the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO), and Charles Gituai, posted as Ambassador/Permanent Representative to the Inter-Government Authority for Development (IGAD).